trans-unit.source: Contains a collection of <xref href="System.String"></xref> objects.

The <xref:System.Drawing.Printing.PrinterSettings.InstalledPrinters%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property, which indicates the names of printers installed on a computer, is a <xref:System.Drawing.Printing.PrinterSettings.StringCollection>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Printing.PrinterSettings.StringCollection"></xref> class.
An array of type <xref href="System.String"></xref>.
Adds a string to the end of the collection.
The string to add to the collection.
The zero-based index of the newly added item.
Copies the contents of the current <xref href="System.Drawing.Printing.PrinterSettings.PrinterResolutionCollection"></xref> to the specified array, starting at the specified index
A zero-based array that receives the items copied from the <xref href="System.Drawing.Printing.PrinterSettings.StringCollection"></xref>.
The index at which to start copying items.
Gets the number of strings in the collection.
The number of strings in the collection.
Returns an enumerator that can iterate through the collection.
This method instantiates an enumerator that takes a snapshot of the current state of the collection.
The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection, so multiple enumerators can have access to the same collection at the same time.

Therefore, any changes made to the collection, either directly or through another enumerator, can cause <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to throw an exception.
Two enumerators instantiated from the same collection at the same time can contain different snapshots of the collection.
Removing objects from the enumerator also removes them from the collection.
An <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> for the <xref href="System.Drawing.Printing.PrinterSettings.StringCollection"></xref>.
Gets the <xref href="System.String"></xref> at a specified index.
The index of the <xref href="System.String"></xref> to get.
The <xref href="System.String"></xref> at the specified index.
